    <section class="section bg-light py-5" id="inequality-and-suicide">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row margin-bottom">
                <div class="col-lg-4">
                    <div class="heading heading--primary"><span class="heading__pre-title">Programs</span>
                        <h2 class="heading__title no-margin-bottom"><span>Inequality </span> <span>& suicide</span></h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-8">
                    <p>People living in the most disadvantaged communities face the highest risk of dying by suicide.</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Financial instability and poverty can increase suicide risk. Suicide is a major inequality issue.</li>
                        <li>Income and unmanageable debt, unemployment, poor housing conditions, and other socioeconomic factors all contribute to high suicide rates.</li>
                        <li>Tackling inequality should be central to suicide prevention and support should be targeted to the poorest groups who are likely to need it most.</li>
                        <li>There is need to create a more human and person-centered whole system approach. This includes a system that is more aware of mental health issues and the economic challenges people face.</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="section py-5" id="young-people-and-suicide">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row margin-bottom">
                <div class="col-lg-4">
                    <div class="heading heading--primary"><span class="heading__pre-title">Programs</span>
                        <h2 class="heading__title no-margin-bottom"><span>Young people </span> <span>& suicide</span></h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-8">
                    <p class="causes__heading-text"> Around 100 young people die by suicide every year. Our report investigates the relationship between loneliness and suicide in young people, and if or how they may be connected.</p>
                    <p class="causes__heading-text">We spoke to young people across different parts of Kenya. Most of them told us that their loneliness played a role in causing their suicidal thoughts.</p>
                    <p class="causes__heading-text">Worryingly, many of them said they didn’t feel able to ask for help with loneliness because of the surrounding stigma. And when people did ask for help, it often wasn’t available or suitable for their needs.</p>
                    <p class="causes__heading-text">There is rarely one reason for a person to feel suicidal. Just as with suicide, loneliness is complex – it is a personal experience that's different for every person. Nevertheless, we found that, across the population, there is an association between suicide and loneliness.</p>
                    <p class="causes__heading-text"><strong>What we are doing:</strong></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>There is need to listen to what young people are telling us: many of them are struggling with loneliness. Loneliness can be a serious health issue; preventing it could be an important part of suicide prevention.</li>
                        <li>As an organization we have set out ambitious targets across to improve wellbeing in young people, including tackling loneliness.</li>
                        <li>We have different campaigns to tackle stigma that young people are experiencing around loneliness.</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
